question_content.description:
### Problem08
Look at the line below:

```java
StdOut.printf("%-9.3f",3.1415926);
```

**Choices:**

Which choices are right?

a. The output of the line will be "____3.142" ("_" stands for space).

b. The output of the line will be "3.142____" ("_" stands for space).

c. In the format string of StdOut.printf(), the conversion specification can be omitted.

d. If the line changes to "StdOut.printf("%.3f",3.1415926);", the output will be "3.141"

e. If the line changes to "StdOut.printf("%.3f",3.1415926);", the output will be "3.142".
choices: a. The output of the line will be "    3.142".
b. The output of the line will be "3.142    ".
c. In the format string of StdOut.printf(), the conversion specification can be omitted.
d. If the line changes to "StdOut.printf("%.3f",3.1415926);", the output will be "3.141"
e. If the line changes to "StdOut.printf("%.3f",3.1415926);", the output will be "3.142".
